      Search                 View Menu  Down arrow icon            Breadcrumbs   College of Nursing    Programs & Applying    Cost & Financial Aid        Cost & Financial Aid  Education is an investment in yourself and your future, and we know it's a big one.  For every student, costs are a major factor in making the decision about where to get that next degree or certificate. Here we provide links to "the horse's mouth," so to speak —the university-level webpages where tuition and fee information is kept up-to-date in real time. We want you to have the most accurate information at your fingertips to make your decision well informed.       Tuition   Traditional BSN  Undergraduate program tuition and fees are set by the university. Detailed tuition information can be found at the website of the UIC Office of the Registrar .  The rates found on this site are for the Chicago campus only; students on other campuses may have variances in rates. Consult the director of your selected campus— Springfield or Urbana —for additional details.  RN to BSN  The online RN to BSN program charges e-tuition rates. Detailed tuition information can be found on the RN to BSN program page .  MS Programs: Graduate-Entry or Bachelor’s to MS  Graduate program base tuition and fees are set by the university. Detailed tuition information can be found at the website of the UIC Office of the Registrar . Nursing tuition includes base tuition, differential and applicable fees and assessments.  The rates found on this site are for the Chicago campus only and students on other campuses may have variances in rates. Consult the director at your selected campus for additional details.  DNP and Post-DNP Certificates  Professional program base tuition and fees are set by the university. Detailed information can be found at the website of the UIC Office of the Registrar . Professional nursing tuition includes base tuition and applicable fees and assessments.  The rates found on this site are for the Chicago campus only and students on other campuses may have variances in rates. Consult the director at your selected campus for additional details.  PhD  Doctoral (graduate) program base tuition and fees are set by the university. Detailed tuition information can be found at the website of the UIC Office of the Registrar . Nursing tuition includes base tuition, differential and applicable fees and assessments.  Certificates  Certificates* charge online tuition rates instead of the range tuition listed. The current online tuition rate can be found at the website of the UIC Office of the Registrar . Students in online tuition programs are not eligible for university health insurance nor can they use the university’s health centers.  * The exception is the post-DNP certificate, which charges professional tuition; please see information above for DNP programs       Financing Your Education     Financial Aid   UIC’s Office of Student Financial Aid helps students understand financial need, apply for federal financial aid (based on the Free Application for Federal Aid, or FAFSA), and identify additional sources of aid such as grants and student employment.      Learn more about financial aid support at UIC       Scholarships   UIC and the College of Nursing provide financial support to undergraduate and graduate students in the form of scholarships. Awards, which vary in levels and lengths, are made every academic year to new and continuing students, who are invited to apply each spring. Applications for UIC Nursing scholarships are evaluated on the basis of academic achievement, financial need and leadership/service experience.      Learn more about scholarships       Graduate Assistantships   Teaching, research and graduate assistantships for graduate students are awarded by individual faculty members and academic departments. Stipends vary based on the percent of time appointed, with appointments between 25% and 67% eligible to receive a base tuition and service fee waiver. Assistantships do not always cover the nursing differential.      Learn more about assistantships at UIC               Programs & Applying    Back to main content           Find Your Program     Bachelor of Science in Nursing     Traditional BSN     Meet BSN students    Admissions & Applying     Admission Requirements    Apply Now      Sample Schedule    Clinical Experiences    BSN Info Sessions      RN to BSN      Master of Science for non-RNs     Meet AGMS/Grad-Entry Students    Clinical Experiences    Admission Requirements    Apply Now    MS Info Sessions      Master of Science for RNs     Meet MS Students    AGMS Transition Program    Admission Requirements    Apply Now    MS Info Sessions      Doctor of Nursing Practice     Meet DNP Students    DNP Focus Areas     Adult-Gerontology Acute Care Nurse Practitioner    Adult-Gerontology Primary Care Nurse Practitioner    Advanced Population Health Nursing    Family Nurse Practitioner    Health Systems Leadership and Informatics    Neonatal Nurse Practitioner     Life as an NNP      Nurse-Midwifery    Nurse-Midwifery / Women's Health Nurse Practitioner    Pediatric Nurse Practitioner – Acute Care    Pediatric Nurse Practitioner – Primary Care    Psychiatric-Mental Health Nurse Practitioner    Women’s Health Nurse Practitioner      The DNP Project     Impactful DNP Projects    Post-Master’s DNP Projects      Post-Master's DNP    Admission Requirements    DNP vs PhD    Apply Now    DNP Info Sessions      Doctor of Philosophy     Meet PhD Students    Sample Program Plans    Admission Requirements    DNP vs PhD    Apply Now      Certificate Programs     Post-DNP Certificate     Apply Now      School Nurse     Info Sessions    School Nurse Certificate Requirements    Admission Requirements    Apply Now    Be a Preceptor      Advanced Practice Palliative Care Nursing    Sleep Health    Teaching/Learning in Nursing and Health Sciences    Applying for Certificates      Concentrations     Primary Care Mental Health Concentr